{
  "abstract": "In a field study in 1994-95 at 6 sites in Sri Lanka, Maruca testulalis [M. vitrata], Helicoverpa armigera, Exelastis sp., Lampides sp., Melanagromyza obtusa, Mylabris sp. and Sphenoptera sp. were identified as pests of pigeon peas. Of these, the most damaging was M. vitrata.",
